><span>啸</span>字的康熙字典解释</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>【丑集上】【口字部】　嘯； 康熙笔画：15； 页码：<a href=\"https://images.yw11.com/kangxi/0196.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><span>页196第26</span></a><br>【唐韻】【正韻】蘇弔切【集韻】【韻會】先弔切，?音熽。【說文】吹聲也。【詩·召南】其嘯也歌。【箋】嘯，蹙口而出聲。又【小雅】嘯歌傷懷。【司馬相如·上林賦】長嘯哀鳴。【拾遺記】前漢，西方有因霄之國，人皆善嘯。丈夫嘯聞百里，婦人嘯聞五十里。【世說新語】蘇門山中忽有眞人，阮籍往觀，對之長嘯良久，乃笑曰：可更作籍。後嘯意盡退，還半嶺許，聞上唒然有聲，如數部鼓吹，林谷傳響，顧看，乃向人嘯也。　又【集韻】息六切，音肅。吹氣若歌。【詩·王風】有女仳離，條其歗矣。【釋文】歗，本亦作嘯。　又【集韻】【正韻】?尺栗切。與叱同。【禮·內則】不嘯不指。詳前叱字註。唒字从口从酋。嘯字十六畫。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>啸</span>字的源字形</div>\n    <div>\n      <p></p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>啸</span>字的起名意思</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>：1、啸引，啸召，呼唤，召唤，长鸣；2、自然界发出的声音。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"yw11_en_transl\">Howl<br>Basic explanation of words<br>Howl<br>(Howl)<br>xiào<br>Pinch the mouth and whistle: Xiao Ge (chanting). Xiaoao. Xiao Gathering (greeting each other, gathering together, such as \"Xiao Xiao Shan Forest\"). Howl. Looking up to the sky and screaming.<br>The animal screamed: Howl of the tiger. Ape Xiao.<br>The sound of nature: the north wind howls. Tsunami.<br>The sound of an airplane or bullet passing by: the airplane screamed and rushed into the blue sky. Cannonballs roared past.<br>Howl<br>Chinese dictionary definition of words<br>Howl<br>Howl<br>English translation of words<br>◎ Howl<br>howl, whistle<br>Howl<br>Kangxi dictionary interpretation of words<br>[Chou Ji 1] [Words Department] 　xiao; Kangxi strokes: 15; page number: page 196 26<br>[Tang Yun] [Zheng Yun] Su Hanging Cut [Ji Yun] [Rhyme Meeting] Hang and cut first,? Yin Qi. [Said the text] Blow the sound too. 【Poetry·Zhaonan】Its Xiao also sings. [Jan] Howl, frowning. And [Xiaoya] Xiaoge is sad. 【Sima Xiangru·Shanglin Fu】Chang Xiao and wailing. [Supplementary Notes] In the former Han Dynasty, there was a country of Yinxiao in the West, and everyone was good at howling. The husband screamed for a hundred miles, and the woman screamed for fifty miles. [Shi Shuo Xin Yu] Sumen Mountain suddenly has a man, Ruan Ji looks forward to it, and screams at him for a long time, but laughs and says: You can write more. After that, the whistling intention retreated, half Ling Xu was returned, and there was no sound when he heard the sound, as in the preaching of several parts, Lin Gu heard the sound, and looked at it, but screamed to others.　[Jiyun] Six cuts of interest, sound and sound. Blow like a song. [Poetry·Wang Feng] There is a female divorce, and it's pretty straightforward. [Explanation] Xiao, this book is also called Xiao.　 [Ji Yun] [Zheng Yun]? Chi chestnut cut. Same as Chi. [Li·NeiZe] Do not scream, do not point. Please refer to the previous note. The word is from the mouth from the chieftain. Sixteen strokes of howling characters.<br>Howl<br>Source glyph<br>Howl<br>Name meaning<br>:1. Howling, howling, calling, calling, long chirping; 2. Sounds from the natural world.</div>\n</div>\n<div><a href=\"https://images.yw11.com/zixing/zi148275976552641.png\" target=\"_blank\"><object data=\"https://images.yw11.com/zixing/zi148275976552641.png\" type=\"image/png\"><img src=\"yw11-zixing-zi148275976552641.png\"></object></a></div>\n<div class=\"two_children__horiz_even\">\n  <div id=\"yw11_image_chinese\">啸<br>会意字。从口,像口(嘴)形,表示口中发出啸声;从肅(肃),肃有严整义,表示啸声长、清脆,严整不杂乱,也表示啸<br>声使人肃然。嘯简化为啸。本义是撮口作声。<br>D(人)撮口作声;打口哨:长~。2兽类长声吼叫:虎~。<br>3形容某种声响:呼~|海~。<br>~傲 ~聚 ~鸣 ~声 海~ 呼~ 虎~猿啼<br>xiào<br>嘯<br>嘯,啸<br>隶<br>「楷)<br>in i ip 指將</div>\n  <div id=\"yw11_image_ru_transl\">Вой<br>Зная слово.<br>Изо рта, как форма рта (рта), это означает, что во рту раздается воющий звук; от су (су) идет строгое и прямое значение, что означает, что вой длинный, четкий, строгий. и не грязный, и это также означает, что вой внушает благоговение.<br>Сяо превращается в Сяо.<br>Первоначальный смысл - высказаться.<br>D (человек) шумит; свист: длинный ~.<br>2 Зверь рычит: Тигр ~.<br>3 Опишите определенный звук: ху ~ | хай ~.<br>~ Гордый ~ Джу ~ Мин ~ Шэн Хай ~ Ху ~ Тигр ~ Крик обезьяны<br>Вой<br>Вой, вой<br>писец<br>«Кай)<br>в я ip означает</